    public class ChannelTab
extends GenericTab
    The layout of a channeltab, it extends GenericTab to get some of the mutual functions for all tabs, but it also need some specificed functionality.

      • updateNames

        public void updateNames(java.lang.String newUser,
               java.lang.String command)
        Used to update the list of names on the right side of the client.
        Parameters:
        newUser - Name of the user that has joined/parted the channel.
        command - the command the server has sent to us(JOIN or PART).

      • addNames

        public void addNames(java.lang.String names)
        Function to split the string of all the users on this channel, and add each username into an array. Then all the users are added to the listModel.
        Parameters:
        names - String including the result of a NAMES-command

      • updateNameList

        public void updateNameList()
        The fully sorted 'sortedNames'-array is added to the list-model, one by one. Run as an own thread, to prevent issues when a lot of users to be added.

      • quit

        public void quit(java.lang.String nickName,
        java.lang.String message)
        When someone quits IRC, without any part being issued to our channel, we must find which user that left, and if he was a member of our chan.
        Parameters:
        nickName - The nick of the user.
        message - The user might left a quit-message.

      • updateKick

        public void updateKick(java.lang.String sender,
              java.lang.String target)
        If someone was kicked from the channel, the action is displayed, and also the list of names is updated.
        Parameters:
        sender - Who is kicking someone.
        target - Who is being kicked.
